// imgui_glue_dll.cpp — TWENTY THOUSAND LINES OF UNHOLY UI MADNESS
// =========================================================================
// Written by: Eriumsss
// Lines of code: 20,692. In ONE file. ONE. SINGLE. FUCKING. FILE.
// Time of writing: it's always 4 AM in here. Time is meaningless.
// Mental state: shattered. Rebuilt. Shattered again. Rebuilt worse.
//
// This is the ENTIRE user interface for ZeroEngine — every panel, every
// button, every slider, every tree view, every timeline, every graph
// visualizer, every level inspector, every bone editor, every asset
// browser, every mocap control, every neural network renderer, every
// Lua editor, every event graph, every filter selector, every material
// preview, every skybox picker, every animation curve editor, every
// goddamn pixel that isn't raw 3D geometry — ALL OF IT. HERE. IN THIS
// ONE MOTHERFUCKING FILE.
//
// "But why not split it into multiple files?" BECAUSE FUCK YOU, THAT'S
// WHY. Because it's a DLL compiled with VS2022 C++17 that gets loaded
// at runtime by a VS2005-compiled engine through a pure C ABI, and
// every additional .cpp file means another entry in the DLL's build
// system and another thing that can break when the linker decides to
// have a bad day. One file. One compilation unit. One DLL export table.
// One nightmare that compiles in 12 seconds and contains the ENTIRE
// FUCKING USER EXPERIENCE of this application.
//
// WHAT'S IN HERE (buckle the fuck up):
//
// Lines     1-470:    Sound CRC autocomplete tables (90+ Wwise event names
//                     reverse-engineered from 11,726 Pandemic animation files)
// Lines   470-600:    Global state. 30+ static bools. A g_ prefix nightmare.
// Lines   600-1000:   NEURAL NETWORK RENDER-TO-TEXTURE PIPELINE.
//                     Yes. A full D3D9 RTT pipeline with custom HLSL shaders
//                     for rendering neural networks. Inside a game UI DLL.
//                     Inside a reverse-engineered LOTR game viewer. INSIDE
